[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mA libFuzzer run terminated with a “timeout” error. The fuzzer did not complete its [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcurrent test case within the allotted time limit and aborted the session.[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- What the issue is  [0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  During a libFuzzer-based testing session against the provided harness, the fuzzer[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mencountered one or more inputs that caused the target code to exceed libFuzzer’s [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mper-test timeout threshold. As a result, libFuzzer halted execution and reported [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m“ERROR: libFuzzer: timeout.”[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Vulnerability type  [0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  No explicit security vulnerability [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., memory corruption[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m is reported in the [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39merror message itself. Instead, the issue manifests as a hang or excessive execution[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtime, which may indicate a potential performance problem or denial-of-service‐style[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbehavior under certain inputs.[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Important observations and findings  [0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The timeout indicates that the code under test failed to return control to [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlibFuzzer within the configured time limit, suggesting a long-running or infinite [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mloop, blocking operation, or heavy computation for specific inputs.  [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The error originates from libFuzzer’s watchdog mechanism, not from an assertion[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mor crash inside the code under test.  [0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • No stack trace or input data is provided in the timeout message, so additional [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlogging or instrumentation may be required to capture the problematic input and [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcall stack.[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Code areas to investigate  [0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. Fuzzer harness entry point – review how inputs are fed into the target [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfunctions and whether the harness can introduce blocking behavior [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msynchronous I/O, locks[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. Core algorithms and loops – locate loops, recursive functions, or state [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmachines within the target code that may not terminate or that scale poorly with [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcertain inputs.  [0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m. External calls or resources – identify any file, network, or system calls [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minvoked by the code under test that could block indefinitely.  [0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m. Timeout configuration – verify libFuzzer’s `-[0m[33mtimeout[0m[39m=` setting and any [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moverrides in the build or test scripts that affect the per-test time limit.  [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mA holistic investigation should combine fuzzer logs, any captured inputs, and code [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreview of the above components to pinpoint where execution stalls and which inputs [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtrigger the timeout.[0m                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m192[0m[39m:            [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m We could possibly implement a more intelligent algorithm if [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnecessary[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m193[0m[39m:            else if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mnextChar == [0m[32m'e'[0m[39m && [0m[1;35mparser.isString[0m[1;39m([0m[39mendobjString[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m194[0m[39m:            [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m195[0m[39m:                currentOffset += endobjString.length;[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m196[0m[39m:                [0m[1;35msource.seek[0m[1;39m([0m[39mcurrentOffset[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m197[0m[39m:                if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mparser.isEOF[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m198[0m[39m:                [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m199[0m[39m:                    endOfObjFound = true;[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m200[0m[39m:                [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m201[0m[39m:                else if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mparser.isString[0m[1;39m([0m[39mendobjRemainingString[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m202[0m[39m:                [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m203[0m[39m:                    currentOffset += endobjRemainingString.length;[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m204[0m[39m:                    endOfObjFound = true;[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m205[0m[39m:                [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m206[0m[39m:            [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m207[0m[39m:        [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m while [0m[1;39m([0m[39mcurrentOffset < lastEOFMarker && ![0m[1;35mparser.isEOF[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Root Cause and Symptom Identification  [0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The fuzzer timeouts are caused by BruteForceParser’s unbounded byte‐by‐byte [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mscanning loops [0m[1;39m([0m[39mparticularly in bfSearchForObjects[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m that, on malformed or large [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minputs, iterate from the start of the file all the way to the EOF marker without [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39many upper bound.  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This exhaustive search can take arbitrarily long [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mO[0m[1;39m([0m[39mn[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m per input[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and thus [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mhits libFuzzer’s per‐test timeout threshold.[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Core Logic to Preserve  [0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The ability to recover from missing or malformed cross‐references in lenient [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmode via brute‐force scanning must remain.  [0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Configuration via system properties [0m[1;39m([0m[39mas in `setEOFLookupRange`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m should be [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpreserved and extended so users can tune this behavior.  [0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - All existing parsing branches, exception flows, and fallback logic in [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mCOSParser.retrieveTrailer[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m should remain intact, so no change to harness or [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mhigh‐level error handling.[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Patch Strategy: Introducing a Search‐Length Cap in BruteForceParser  [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   a. Add a new configurable constant near the top of BruteForceParser.java:[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```java[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[35m/[0m[39m** [0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       * Maximum number of bytes to scan in brute‐force object search.[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       * Default [0m[1;36m10[0m[39m MB; override with system property [0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       * [0m[32m'org.apache.pdfbox.pdfparser.bruteforce.maxSearchLength'[0m[39m.[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       *[0m[35m/[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      private static final long MAX_SEARCH_LENGTH =[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          [0m[1;35mLong.getLong[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"org.apache.pdfbox.pdfparser.bruteforce.maxSearchLength"[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m10[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m* [0m[1;36m1024[0m[39m * 1024L[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   b. In [0m[1;35mbfSearchForObjects[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, after obtaining `lastEOFMarker`, compute a hard [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlimit for scanning:[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```java[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      long startOffset = MINIMUM_SEARCH_OFFSET;[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      long scanLimit = [0m[1;35mMath.min[0m[1;39m([0m[39mlastEOFMarker, startOffset + MAX_SEARCH_LENGTH[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   c. Change the loop condition to stop at `scanLimit` rather than `lastEOFMarker`:[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```java[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      do [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m existing body[0m[33m...[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m while [0m[1;39m([0m[39mcurrentOffset < scanLimit && ![0m[1;35mparser.isEOF[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   d. Immediately after the loop, detect if the loop terminated because of the cap [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39mi.e., `currentOffset >= scanLimit` and EOF not reached[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```java[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mcurrentOffset >= scanLimit && ![0m[1;35mparser.isEOF[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          throw new [0m[1;35mIOException[0m[1;39m([0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m              [0m[32m"Brute‐force search for PDF objects exceeded maximum allowed bytes of[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32m"[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m              + MAX_SEARCH_LENGTH + [0m[32m" bytes, aborted."[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   e. Apply a similar cap to any other full‐file brute‐force scanning methods in [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mBruteForceParser [0m[1;39m([0m[39mfor example, [0m[1;35mbfSearchForObjStreams[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, reusing the same [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`MAX_SEARCH_LENGTH`.[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Exception Flow and Fuzzing Impact  [0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The thrown IOException is caught by [0m[1;35mCOSParser.retrieveTrailer[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:  [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     – In lenient mode, [0m[1;35mretrieveTrailer[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m will attempt to rebuild the trailer but [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwill hit the same cap and rethrow, leading to a fast failure rather than a hang.  [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     – In strict mode, the exception propagates immediately.  [0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Under fuzzing, inputs that once hung the parser will now fail quickly [0m[1;39m([0m[39min [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbounded time[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, avoiding the libFuzzer timeout.  [0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No harness or test code needs modification. All tests continue to exercise [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlenient parsing, and users can still override `bruteforce.maxSearchLength` to [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39maccommodate larger but valid PDFs.[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Configuration and Documentation  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Add Javadoc for the new system property in BruteForceParser.java.  [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Update PDFBox’s user guide to mention the new property [0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`org.apache.pdfbox.pdfparser.bruteforce.maxSearchLength` and its default.  [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Provide a unit test that constructs a synthetic RandomAccessRead stream longer[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthan [0m[1;36m10[0m[39m MB lacking valid ‘obj’ markers; verify that bfSearchForObjects aborts [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwithin milliseconds and throws the expected IOException.[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. Justification and Trade‐offs  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - By bounding the brute‐force scan, we eliminate the root cause of the fuzzer [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtimeouts while preserving lenient parsing for typical PDF sizes.  [0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The default [0m[1;36m10[0m[39m MB cap covers most legitimate PDFs; edge cases needing deeper [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mrecovery can raise the limit via system property.  [0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This approach mirrors the existing EOF lookup configurability [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39m`org.apache.pdfbox.pdfparser.nonSequentialPDFParser.eofLookupRange`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, maintaining [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconsistency in design.[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m7[0m[39m. Side Effects and Mitigations  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Very large, severely malformed PDFs may no longer have all objects recovered [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39munder the default cap; instead, the parser fails fast.  [0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - To mitigate, users parsing truly large PDFs can raise [0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`bruteforce.maxSearchLength`.  [0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Performance on well‐formed PDFs [0m[1;39m([0m[39m<[0m[1;36m10[0m[39m MB[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m is unaffected.  [0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m8[0m[39m. Summary of File Changes  [0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   <code_range>pdfbox/src/main/java/org/apache/pdfbox/pdfparser/BruteForceParser.ja[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mva: add MAX_SEARCH_LENGTH constant<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_range[0m[39m>  [0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   <code_range>pdfbox/src/main/java/org/apache/pdfbox/pdfparser/BruteForceParser.ja[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mva: [0m[1;35mbfSearchForObjects[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, adjust loop guard and post‐loop exception<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_range[0m[39m>  [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe initial issue reported by libFuzzer is a persistent timeout during fuzz testing[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mof the PDFBox parser. In response, a patch was introduced that limits the [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbrute-force object search to a maximum number of bytes [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdefault [0m[1;36m10[0m[39m MB, configurable[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mvia a system property[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and aborts with an IOException if that limit is exceeded. [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAfter applying the patch, the libFuzzer harness still reports a timeout without [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mproceeding further or producing additional log output.[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Initial Issue  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - During fuzz testing with libFuzzer, execution consistently stalls and [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39meventually triggers a timeout.  [0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The only visible error is:  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     “ERROR: libFuzzer: timeout”  [0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - There is no stack trace or parser-specific error message in the fuzzer output.[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Observations on the Initial Issue  [0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The PDF parser appears to enter a lengthy or infinite loop when scanning for [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mobjects in corrupted or malformed inputs.  [0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No direct indication that file I/O fails; the harness simply waits until the [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtimeout threshold is reached.  [0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The brute-force search routine [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[1;35mbfSearchForObjects[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m is a likely hotspot, [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mas it contains an unbounded loop over file offsets.[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Patch Attempt  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Introduced a new constant, `MAX_SEARCH_LENGTH`, defaulting to [0m[1;36m10[0m[39m MB [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m10[0m[39m × [0m[1;36m1024[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m× [0m[1;36m1024[0m[39m bytes[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, overrideable via system property  [0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     `org.apache.pdfbox.pdfparser.bruteforce.maxSearchLength`.  [0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Modified local variables in `[0m[1;35mbfSearchForObjects[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`:  [0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Renamed `currentOffset` initialization to use `startOffset = [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mMINIMUM_SEARCH_OFFSET`.  [0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Computed `scanLimit = [0m[1;35mmin[0m[1;39m([0m[39mlastEOFMarker, startOffset + MAX_SEARCH_LENGTH[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`. [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Changed the loop condition from `currentOffset < lastEOFMarker` to [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`currentOffset < scanLimit`.  [0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - After the loop, if `currentOffset >= scanLimit` and the parser is not at EOF, [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39man IOException is thrown indicating the search exceeded the maximum allowed bytes.[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Result After Applying the Patch  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The fuzzer run still results in “ERROR: libFuzzer: timeout.”  [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No new IOException message is visible in the fuzzer log, suggesting the [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexception path may not be reached before the timeout or is not surfaced by the [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mharness.  [0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The behavior of the harness [0m[1;39m([0m[39mstalling until timeout[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m remains unchanged.[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Areas for Further Investigation  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The `[0m[1;35mbfSearchForObjects[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method, particularly:  [0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • `[0m[1;35mbfSearchForLastEOFMarker[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` implementation and its return value semantics. [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • The loop body in `[0m[1;35mbfSearchForObjects[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` that advances `currentOffset`—ensure[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moffsets are incremented under all conditions.  [0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Interaction between parser state [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[1;35mparser.isEOF[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and the new exception [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpath—confirm the exception is thrown and propagated.  [0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The fuzzer harness entry point to verify whether IOExceptions are caught or [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mignored, potentially causing silent stalls.  [0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - File source abstraction [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[1;35msource.getPosition[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, `source.read[0m[33m...[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to check [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfor blocking I/O or retries.  [0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Any other loops in the parsing pipeline [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., cross-reference table search[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthat might also be unbounded under malformed inputs.[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Initial Issue Log[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mHere is the initial issue log of the codebase:[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<issue>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mERROR: libFuzzer: timeout[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95missue[0m[39m>[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Additional Issue Log[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mHere is the additional issue log after the last patch attempt:[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<additional_issue>[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mERROR: libFuzzer: timeout[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95madditional_issue[0m[39m>[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Notes[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- All patch attempts are applied to the initial codebase. Reapply the the previous [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpatches if needed.[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- If multiple different issues are present, all the issues must be resolved in a [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msingle patch attempt.[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Try different approaches to resolve the issues.[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Analysis [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Analysis Report[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Relevant Code Snippets[0m                                                           [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m136[0m[39m:        long currentOffset = MINIMUM_SEARCH_OFFSET;[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m137[0m[39m:        long lastObjectId = Long.MIN_VALUE;[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m138[0m[39m:        int lastGenID = Integer.MIN_VALUE;[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m139[0m[39m:        long lastObjOffset = Long.MIN_VALUE;[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m140[0m[39m:        char[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[39m endobjString = [0m[32m"ndo"[0m[1;35m.toCharArray[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m141[0m[39m:        char[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[39m endobjRemainingString = [0m[32m"bj"[0m[1;35m.toCharArray[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpdfbox/src/main/java/org/apache/pdfbox/pdfparser/BruteForceParser.jav[0m[1;92ma:142[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m147[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m142[0m[39m:        boolean endOfObjFound = false;[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m143[0m[39m:        do[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m144[0m[39m:        [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m145[0m[39m:            [0m[1;35msource.seek[0m[1;39m([0m[39mcurrentOffset[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m146[0m[39m:            int nextChar = [0m[1;35msource.read[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m147[0m[39m:            currentOffset++;[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpdfbox/src/main/java/org/apache/pdfbox/pdfparser/BruteForceParser.jav[0m[1;92ma:207[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m214[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m207[0m[39m:        [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m while [0m[1;39m([0m[39mcurrentOffset < lastEOFMarker && ![0m[1;35mparser.isEOF[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m208[0m[39m:        if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m([0m[39mlastEOFMarker < Long.MAX_VALUE || endOfObjFound[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m && lastObjOffset [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m> [0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m209[0m[39m:        [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m210[0m[39m:            [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m if the pdf wasn't cut off in the middle or if the last object [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mends with a [0m[32m"endobj"[0m[39m marker[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m211[0m[39m:            [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m the last object id has to be added here so that it can't get [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlost as there isn't any subsequent object id[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m212[0m[39m:            [0m[1;35mbfSearchCOSObjectKeyOffsets.put[0m[1;39m([0m[39mnew [0m[1;35mCOSObjectKey[0m[1;39m([0m[39mlastObjectId, [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlastGenID[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m,[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m213[0m[39m:                    lastObjOffset[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m214[0m[39m:        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Root Cause Analysis:[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The previous patch correctly bounded the main object‐search loop in [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mbfSearchForObjects[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m but did not bound the initial search for the last “%%EOF” [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmarker. In malformed PDFs lacking an EOF marker, [0m[1;35mbfSearchForLastEOFMarker[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m still [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mloops unbounded over the entire file, causing the parser to hang before [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mbfSearchForObjects[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m ever executes.[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Additionally, even if [0m[1;35mbfSearchForObjects[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m throws an IOException upon [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexceeding MAX_SEARCH_LENGTH, that exception is caught and suppressed in PDFParser’s[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfallback logic, preventing the fuzzer harness from seeing any error and leading [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39magain to a silent stall.[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Strategy to Fix the EOF Search and Surface Errors:[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   A. Introduce the same MAX_SEARCH_LENGTH bound in [0m[1;35mbfSearchForLastEOFMarker[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. Declare DEFAULT_MAX_SEARCH_LENGTH and read system property [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`org.apache.pdfbox.pdfparser.bruteforce.maxSearchLength` at the top of [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mBruteForceParser.[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. In [0m[1;35mbfSearchForLastEOFMarker[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, replace its unbounded loop with a loop that[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstops once the position exceeds MINIMUM_SEARCH_OFFSET + MAX_SEARCH_LENGTH or EOF is[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreached. If the bound is hit without finding “%%EOF”, immediately return the bound [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39mso [0m[1;35mbfSearchForObjects[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m uses a finite lastEOFMarker[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m. If the bound is exceeded and no EOF marker is found, log a warning and [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mproceed with lastEOFMarker = startOffset + MAX_SEARCH_LENGTH.[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   B. Allow the IOException from [0m[1;35mbfSearchForObjects[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to escape [0m[1;35mPDFParser.parse[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. In PDFParser [0m[1;39m([0m[39mthe main entry‐point[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, locate the try/catch block around the[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbrute‐force fallback. Change it to either:[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         • Catch the new IOException specifically and rethrow it as an unchecked [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexception [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., wrap in IllegalStateException[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. [0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         • Or simply remove the catch so the IOException propagates.[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. This ensures that during fuzzing, hitting the search limit triggers a [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mvisible error rather than suppressed silent parsing.[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   C. Preserve Existing Functionality:[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - All existing markers, object‐search logic, and cross‐reference handling [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mremain intact.[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - The MAX_SEARCH_LENGTH default [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m10[0m[39m MB[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and system‐property override remain [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconfigurable as before.[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Fuzz harness code is not modified; it will now observe an exception instead[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mof hanging.[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Detailed Implementation Steps:[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. In BruteForceParser [0m[1;39m([0m[39mnear class fields[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Add:[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         ```[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         private static final long DEFAULT_MAX_SEARCH_LENGTH = 10L * [0m[1;36m1024[0m[39m * [0m[1;36m1024[0m[39m;[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         private static final long MAX_SEARCH_LENGTH =[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             [0m[1;35mLong.getLong[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"org.apache.pdfbox.pdfparser.bruteforce.maxSearchLength"[0m[39m,[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                          DEFAULT_MAX_SEARCH_LENGTH[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         ```[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. In [0m[1;35mbfSearchForLastEOFMarker[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Capture `long start = MINIMUM_SEARCH_OFFSET;`[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Compute `long bound = start + MAX_SEARCH_LENGTH;`[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Replace its do/while or for loop so it only scans while `currentPos < [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35msource.length[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` AND `currentPos < bound`.[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - If loop exits due to `currentPos >= bound` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mno EOF found[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, log:[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         `[0m[1;35mLOG.warn[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"EOF marker not found within [0m[32m{[0m[32m}[0m[32m bytes; proceeding with [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32mfallback"[0m[39m, MAX_SEARCH_LENGTH[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;`[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Return `[0m[1;35mMath.min[0m[1;39m([0m[39mfoundEOFOffset, bound[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` so bfSearchForObjects uses a [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfinite `lastEOFMarker`.[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m. In [0m[1;35mbfSearchForObjects[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Already patched to use `scanLimit = [0m[1;35mMath.min[0m[1;39m([0m[39mlastEOFMarker, startOffset + [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mMAX_SEARCH_LENGTH[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Retain the post‐loop check:[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         ```[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mcurrentOffset >= scanLimit && ![0m[1;35mparser.isEOF[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             throw new [0m[1;35mIOException[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"Brute-force search exceeded "[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                 + MAX_SEARCH_LENGTH + [0m[32m" bytes"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         ```[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m. In [0m[1;35mPDFParser.parse[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mor wherever brute-force fallback is invoked[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Locate code similar to:[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         ```[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         try [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m attempt normal parse[0m[33m...[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m catch [0m[1;39m([0m[39mIOException e[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m fallback to brute-force[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             BruteForceParser bf = new [0m[1;35mBruteForceParser[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             [0m[1;35mbf.getBFCOSObjectOffsets[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         ```[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Change to:[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         ```[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         try [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m normal parse[0m[33m...[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m catch [0m[1;39m([0m[39mIOException e[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m fallback[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             BruteForceParser bf = new [0m[1;35mBruteForceParser[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             [0m[1;35mbf.getBFCOSObjectOffsets[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;  [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m may now throw IOException on bound[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         ```[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         Remove any `catch [0m[1;39m([0m[39mIOException[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` around this call so the bound‐triggered [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mIOException propagates to the harness.[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;36m5[0m[39m. Testing & Validation:[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Run existing PDFBox unit tests to ensure no regressions in well-formed [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPDFs.[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Fuzz with inputs designed to exceed [0m[1;36m10[0m[39m MB search area with no “%%EOF”; [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mverify the harness now reports an exception rather than timeout.[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Justification:[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Bounding both the EOF‐marker search and object search ensures no unbounded [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mloops on malformed inputs.[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Surfacing the IOException to the harness converts silent hangs into immediate [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfailures, dramatically reducing fuzz‐test timeouts.[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Existing logic and public APIs remain untouched; only internal parser loops [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mgain size checks.[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - System‐property override provides flexibility, matching original patch intent.[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Side Effects & Mitigations:[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Well‐formed PDFs with valid EOF markers within the first [0m[1;36m10[0m[39m MB are unaffected.[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Very large valid PDFs [0m[1;39m([0m[39mEOF beyond [0m[1;36m10[0m[39m MB[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m may hit the bound; users can raise [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe system property at runtime.[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Logging added in [0m[1;35mbfSearchForLastEOFMarker[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m only warns and proceeds; it does [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnot abort valid cases.[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         ===[33mIssue[0m===                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ERROR: libFuzzer: timeout                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mReport[0m===                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         # Evaluation Report                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ## Summary                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         The project’s fuzzing harness reports a persistent timeout from libFuzzer when      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         exercising PDF parsing code. To address this, a patch was applied to                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `BruteForceParser.java` that introduces a configurable maximum search length for    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         the brute-force object finder. Despite these changes, the fuzzer still times out    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         with the same “ERROR: libFuzzer: timeout” message.                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ## Description                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m. Initial Issue                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            A libFuzzer run targeting the PDFBox parser hangs or takes too long, triggering  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         a timeout. The only output captured is:                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              ERROR: libFuzzer: timeout                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m. Key Observations                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - The failure mode is a generic fuzzer timeout; no stack trace or exception is   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         reported.                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - The brute-force object discovery routine in `BruteForceParser` can scan large  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         file regions in a tight loop, which may be unbounded in length.                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - No other errors or crashes were logged, indicating the parser never reaches a  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         terminal exception or EOF in a timely manner.                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m. Patch Attempt                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            The patch adds two new constants and bounds the brute-force scan window:         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - `DEFAULT_MAX_SEARCH_LENGTH` set to [1;36m10[0m MiB.                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - `MAX_SEARCH_LENGTH` read from system property                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `org.apache.pdfbox.pdfparser.bruteforce.maxSearchLength`.                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            In method `[1;35mbfSearchForObjects[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m`:                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Introduced `startOffset = MINIMUM_SEARCH_OFFSET`.                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Computed `scanLimit = [1;35mmin[0m[1m([0mlastEOFMarker, startOffset + MAX_SEARCH_LENGTH[1m)[0m`.    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Replaced the loop condition `currentOffset [1m<[0m[39m lastEOFMarker` with [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`currentOffset < scanLimit`.  [0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - After the loop, if `currentOffset >= scanLimit` and EOF was not reached, an [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`IOException` is thrown reporting the exceeded limit.[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   Full patched snippet:[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     private static final long DEFAULT_MAX_SEARCH_LENGTH = 10L * [0m[1;36m1024[0m[39m * 1024L;  [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     private static final long MAX_SEARCH_LENGTH =  [0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[1;35mLong.getLong[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"org.apache.pdfbox.pdfparser.bruteforce.maxSearchLength"[0m[39m, [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mDEFAULT_MAX_SEARCH_LENGTH[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     private void [0m[1;35mbfSearchForObjects[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m throws IOException[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         long lastEOFMarker = [0m[1;35mbfSearchForLastEOFMarker[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         long startOffset = MINIMUM_SEARCH_OFFSET;[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         long scanLimit = [0m[1;35mMath.min[0m[1;39m([0m[39mlastEOFMarker, startOffset + MAX_SEARCH_LENGTH[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         long currentOffset = startOffset;[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         …[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m while [0m[1;39m([0m[39mcurrentOffset < scanLimit && ![0m[1;35mparser.isEOF[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mcurrentOffset >= scanLimit && ![0m[1;35mparser.isEOF[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                       [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m299[0m[39m:                [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m stop immediately and return everything read so far[0m           [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m240[0m[39m:            return COSNull.NULL;[0m                                                [2m                [0m
