[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m173[0m[39m:    [0m[1;35mBaseParser[0m[1;39m([0m[39mRandomAccessRead pdfSource[0m[1;39m)[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m174[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m175[0m[39m:        this.source = pdfSource;[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m176[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m177[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m178[0m[39m:    private static boolean [0m[1;35misHexDigit[0m[1;39m([0m[39mchar ch[0m[1;39m)[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m179[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m180[0m[39m:        return [0m[1;35misDigit[0m[1;39m([0m[39mch[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m ||[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m181[0m[39m:        [0m[1;39m([0m[39mch >= [0m[32m'a'[0m[39m && ch <= [0m[32m'f'[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m ||[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m182[0m[39m:        [0m[1;39m([0m[39mch >= [0m[32m'A'[0m[39m && ch <= [0m[32m'F'[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m183[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m184[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m185[0m[39m:    [0m[35m/[0m[39m**[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m186[0m[39m:     * Returns the object key for the given combination of object and [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mgeneration number. The object key from the cross[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m187[0m[39m:     * reference table/stream will be reused if available. Otherwise a newly [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcreated object will be returned.[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m188[0m[39m:     * [0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m189[0m[39m:     * @param num the given object number[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m190[0m[39m:     * @param gen the given generation number[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m191[0m[39m:     * [0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m192[0m[39m:     * @return the COS object key[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m193[0m[39m:     *[0m[35m/[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m194[0m[39m:    protected COSObjectKey [0m[1;35mgetObjectKey[0m[1;39m([0m[39mlong num, int gen[0m[1;39m)[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m195[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m196[0m[39m:        if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdocument == null || [0m[1;35mdocument.getXrefTable[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.isEmpty[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m197[0m[39m:        [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m198[0m[39m:            return new [0m[1;35mCOSObjectKey[0m[1;39m([0m[39mnum, gen[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m199[0m[39m:        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m200[0m[39m:        [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m use a cache to get the COSObjectKey as iterating over the [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mxref-table-map gets slow for big pdfs[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Root Cause Analysis[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The brute‐force parser’s `[0m[1;35mbfSearchForLastEOFMarker[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method scans the entire [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPDF [0m[1;39m([0m[39mfrom `MINIMUM_SEARCH_OFFSET` to EOF[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m via repeated calls to [0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mfindString[0m[1;39m([0m[39mEOF_MARKER[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`. On large or malformed inputs, this unbounded search [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconsumes excessive time, and it’s the primary reason libFuzzer still hits its [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtimeout even after bounding the object‐finding loop.[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Although the previous patch capped the _object search_ to `MAX_SEARCH_LENGTH`,[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe _EOF‐marker search_ remains unbounded and can itself hang or be too slow.[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Key Change: Bound the EOF‐Marker Lookup Window[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Introduce logic in `[0m[1;35mbfSearchForLastEOFMarker[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` to only search within the last[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`MAX_SEARCH_LENGTH` bytes of the file:[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     a[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m Determine the file length via a new `[0m[1;35mparser.getFileLen[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` accessor.[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     b[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m Compute `eofSearchStart = [0m[1;35mmax[0m[1;39m([0m[39mMINIMUM_SEARCH_OFFSET, fileLen – [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mMAX_SEARCH_LENGTH[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     c[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m Seek to `eofSearchStart` and run the existing `[0m[1;35mfindString[0m[1;39m([0m[39mEOF_MARKER[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mloop—thus limiting the scan to at most `MAX_SEARCH_LENGTH`.[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This ensures `[0m[1;35mbfSearchForLastEOFMarker[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` completes in time proportional to [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`MAX_SEARCH_LENGTH` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdefault [0m[1;36m10[0m[39m MiB[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Implementation Steps[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   A. In `COSParser.java` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mpart of the same codebase[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, expose the file length:[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Add:[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[35m/[0m[39m**[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         * Expose the underlying PDF length for bounded searches.[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         *[0m[35m/[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        public long [0m[1;35mgetFileLen[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            return fileLen;[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - This small getter allows `BruteForceParser` to compute the trailing‐bytes [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwindow without breaking encapsulation.[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   B. In `BruteForceParser.java`, patch `[0m[1;35mbfSearchForLastEOFMarker[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`:[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. Compute the bounded start offset:[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         ```[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         long eofSearchStart = MINIMUM_SEARCH_OFFSET;[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         long fileLen = [0m[1;35mparser.getFileLen[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mfileLen > MINIMUM_SEARCH_OFFSET + MAX_SEARCH_LENGTH[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             eofSearchStart = fileLen - MAX_SEARCH_LENGTH;[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[1;35msource.seek[0m[1;39m([0m[39meofSearchStart[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         ```[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. Run the existing `[0m[1;35mfindString[0m[1;39m([0m[39mEOF_MARKER[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` loop from `eofSearchStart`, [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mupdating `lastEOFMarker` as before.[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m. Keep the fallback: if no marker is found, return `Long.MAX_VALUE` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mso [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdownstream object‐search loop still uses its own `MAX_SEARCH_LENGTH` bound[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m. Remove or replace the original unconditional [0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35msource.seek[0m[1;39m([0m[39mMINIMUM_SEARCH_OFFSET[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Preservation of Critical Logic[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - We do **not** alter the object‐finding loop [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[1;35mbfSearchForObjects[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, its EOF [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mchecks, or the existing `MAX_SEARCH_LENGTH` semantics. We merely narrow the _EOF [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmarker lookup_ to the same window already used for object scanning.[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No harness code, fuzzing logic, or utility methods outside `BruteForceParser` [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand the minimal `COSParser` getter are modified—tests and other parsing paths [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mremain unchanged.[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - All existing code paths that rely on `[0m[1;35mbfSearchTriggered[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, `[0m[1;35mparser.isEOF[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mor the `[0m[1;35mbfSearchForObjStreams[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` behavior are untouched.[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Why This Is Optimal[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Bounding the EOF lookup to the trailing `MAX_SEARCH_LENGTH` bytes directly [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mattacks the unbounded scan in `[0m[1;35mbfSearchForLastEOFMarker[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, the longest‐running [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpart of the brute‐force parser.[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - It reuses the already‐introduced `MAX_SEARCH_LENGTH` constant [0m[1;39m([0m[39mand its [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msystem‐property override[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to give users full control over both EOF‐lookup and [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mobject‐search bounds in a consistent manner.[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Similar bounded‐window logic already exists elsewhere in the codebase [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mCOSParser.getStartxrefOffset[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` uses `readTrailBytes` to limit its search[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, so [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthis approach aligns with existing design patterns.[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. Potential Side Effects and Mitigations[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In rare cases where a valid `%%EOF` marker lives further back than [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`MAX_SEARCH_LENGTH` bytes from the true end, `[0m[1;35mbfSearchForLastEOFMarker[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` will not [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfind it, and will fall back to `Long.MAX_VALUE`. The object‐finding loop will then [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdefault to its own [0m[1;36m10[0m[39m MiB bound, so it still terminates in bounded time.[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - If users truly need to scan beyond [0m[1;36m10[0m[39m MiB for EOF due to extreme tail‐padding,[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthey can increase the system property [0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`org.apache.pdfbox.pdfparser.bruteforce.maxSearchLength`, which now governs both [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mEOF lookup and object search.[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m7[0m[39m. References to Similar Code[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `[0m[1;35mCOSParser.getStartxrefOffset[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m307[0m[39m–[0m[1;36m330[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m bounds its scan to the last [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`readTrailBytes` bytes—our new logic parallels that approach.[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The original patch in `[0m[1;35mbfSearchForObjects[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` already correctly uses [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`MAX_SEARCH_LENGTH` to cap the object scan; we now apply the same cap to the [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpreceding EOF‐lookup phase.[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mWith these changes, the brute‐force parser will finish both EOF‐marker discovery [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand object scanning in time proportional to `MAX_SEARCH_LENGTH`, resolving the [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfuzzer’s persistent timeout without altering any harness or test code. [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         search in `BruteForceParser` so that it bounds its search window by the file length [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1m([0musing a presumed `MAX_SEARCH_LENGTH` constant[1m)[0m. After applying the patch,          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         compilation fails with two “cannot find symbol” errors for `MAX_SEARCH_LENGTH` in   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `BruteForceParser`.                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ## Description                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         Initial Issue                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - A libFuzzer run against PDFBox’s parsing components stalled until its timeout     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         threshold.                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - The harness triggered `BruteForceParser` to scan through the PDF stream for EOF   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         markers, but without any bounds on how far back it will search.                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         Important Observations                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - The fuzzer harness simply invokes PDFBox parsing entry points and is not itself   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         modified.                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - Unbounded backward scanning in `BruteForceParser` can cause extremely long loops  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         over large or malformed inputs, leading to a timeout.                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - No existing mechanism exposes the total PDF size [1m([0m`fileLen`[1m)[0m to the low‐level     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         parser.                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         Patch Attempt                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m. In `COSParser.java`, after `document = new [1;35mCOSDocument[0m[1m([0m[33m...[0m[1m)[0m`, a new public       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         method was inserted:                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            ```java                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            [35m/[0m**                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m             * Expose the underlying PDF length for bounded searches.                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m             *[35m/[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            public long [1;35mgetFileLen[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m [1m{[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                return fileLen;                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            [1m}[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            ```                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m. In `BruteForceParser.java`, the initial unconditional                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `[1;35msource.seek[0m[1m([0mMINIMUM_SEARCH_OFFSET[1m)[0m` was replaced with:                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            ```java                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            long fileLen = [1;35mparser.getFileLen[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m;                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            long eofSearchStart = MINIMUM_SEARCH_OFFSET;                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            if [1m([0mfileLen > MINIMUM_SEARCH_OFFSET + MAX_SEARCH_LENGTH[1m)[0m [1m{[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                eofSearchStart = fileLen - MAX_SEARCH_LENGTH;                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            [1m}[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            [1;35msource.seek[0m[1m([0meofSearchStart[1m)[0m;                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            ```                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            The intent is to seek at most `MAX_SEARCH_LENGTH` bytes from the end of the file [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         rather than from a fixed offset at the beginning.                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         Patch Result                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - Compilation errors raised at lines referencing `MAX_SEARCH_LENGTH` in             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `BruteForceParser.java`:                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           “cannot find symbol: variable MAX_SEARCH_LENGTH” [1m([0mtwice[1m)[0m.                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - No other errors; the new method `[1;35mgetFileLen[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m` did not trigger errors, implying   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `fileLen` exists in `COSParser`.                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         Areas for Further Investigation                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - Definition and scope of `MAX_SEARCH_LENGTH`: ensure this constant is declared and [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         visible in `BruteForceParser`.                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - Presence and accessibility of the `fileLen` field in `COSParser` or its           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         superclass to confirm `[1;35mgetFileLen[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m` can compile and return a meaningful value.     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - Interaction between `BruteForceParser` and `COSParser` instances: verify that     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `parser` is the correct object from which to retrieve the file length.              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - Any other scanning loops or unbounded seeks in the PDF parsing code that could    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         contribute to fuzzer timeouts.                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - Integration points in the fuzzer harness to ensure that changes in internal       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         parser APIs are correctly wired into the fuzzing entry path.                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ## Initial Issue Log                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         Here is the initial issue log of the codebase:                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1m<[0m[1;95missue[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mERROR: libFuzzer: timeout[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95missue[0m[39m>[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Additional Issue Log[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mHere is the additional issue log after the last patch attempt:[0m                      [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpdfbox/src/main/java/org/apache/pdfbox/pdfparser/BruteForceParser.jav[0m[1;92ma:50[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m58[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m50[0m[39m:    private static final long MINIMUM_SEARCH_OFFSET = [0m[1;36m6[0m[39m;[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m51[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m52[0m[39m:    [0m[35m/[0m[39m**[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m53[0m[39m:     * EOF-marker.[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m54[0m[39m:     *[0m[35m/[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m55[0m[39m:    private static final char[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[39m EOF_MARKER = [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m [0m[32m'%'[0m[39m, [0m[32m'%'[0m[39m, [0m[32m'E'[0m[39m, [0m[32m'O'[0m[39m, [0m[32m'F'[0m[39m [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m;[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m56[0m[39m:    [0m[35m/[0m[39m**[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m57[0m[39m:     * obj-marker.[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m58[0m[39m:     *[0m[35m/[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpdfbox/src/main/java/org/apache/pdfbox/pdfparser/BruteForceParser.jav[0m[1;92ma:382[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m387[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m382[0m[39m:    private boolean [0m[1;35mbfSearchForTrailer[0m[1;39m([0m[39mCOSDictionary trailer[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m throws [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mIOException[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m383[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m384[0m[39m:        long originOffset = [0m[1;35msource.getPosition[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m385[0m[39m:        [0m[1;35msource.seek[0m[1;39m([0m[39mMINIMUM_SEARCH_OFFSET[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m386[0m[39m:        [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m search for trailer marker[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m387[0m[39m:        long trailerOffset = [0m[1;35mfindString[0m[1;39m([0m[39mTRAILER_MARKER[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Add the missing `MAX_SEARCH_LENGTH` constant to BruteForceParser[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In `pdfbox/src/main/java/org/apache/pdfbox/pdfparser/BruteForceParser.java` [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39mnear the top of the class, alongside `MINIMUM_SEARCH_OFFSET` and `EOF_MARKER`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdefine:[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[35m/[0m[39m**[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      * Maximum number of bytes to scan backwards from end-of-file[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      * when looking for markers.[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      * Reuses the default trailing‐buffer size from COSParser.[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      *[0m[35m/[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     private static final long MAX_SEARCH_LENGTH = [0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mCOSParser.DEFAULT_TRAIL_BYTECOUNT;[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Because `COSParser` and `BruteForceParser` share the same package [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39m`org.apache.pdfbox.pdfparser`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, no additional import is needed.[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Ensure the [0m[1;35mgetFileLen[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m accessor in COSParser is correctly placed[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Verify in `COSParser.java` that the `[0m[1;35mgetFileLen[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method sits at class scope [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39mnot nested inside another method[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and simply returns the private `fileLen` field:[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```java[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[35m/[0m[39m**[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      * Expose the underlying PDF length for bounded searches.[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      *[0m[35m/[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     public long [0m[1;35mgetFileLen[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         return fileLen;[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No changes are needed here if compilation of `[0m[1;35mgetFileLen[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` already succeeds.[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Replace unbounded seeks in trailer search with a bounded window[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In `[0m[1;35mBruteForceParser.bfSearchForTrailer[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, change the initial [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35msource.seek[0m[1;39m([0m[39mMINIMUM_SEARCH_OFFSET[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` to the following block:[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```java[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     long fileLen = [0m[1;35mparser.getFileLen[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     long eofSearchStart = MINIMUM_SEARCH_OFFSET;[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m only back up up to MAX_SEARCH_LENGTH bytes[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mfileLen > MINIMUM_SEARCH_OFFSET + MAX_SEARCH_LENGTH[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         eofSearchStart = fileLen - MAX_SEARCH_LENGTH;[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;35msource.seek[0m[1;39m([0m[39meofSearchStart[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This ensures that on large or malformed PDFs, the parser scans at most [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`MAX_SEARCH_LENGTH` bytes backwards from the file’s end rather than iterating over [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe entire file.[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Review other backward‐search loops[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Grep for any other occurrences of `[0m[1;35msource.seek[0m[1;39m([0m[39mMINIMUM_SEARCH_OFFSET[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` or [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39munbounded backward scans in `BruteForceParser` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mor its helper methods[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Apply the same bounded‐search pattern wherever appropriate to prevent fuzzer [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtimeouts.[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Build and verify[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Recompile the project. The “cannot find symbol: MAX_SEARCH_LENGTH” errors will[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbe resolved by step [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m.[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Run existing unit and integration tests to ensure no behavior regression in [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstandard PDF parsing.[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Re-run the libFuzzer harness to confirm that the EOF‐marker search no longer [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstalls or times out on large inputs.[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mJustification:[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Defining `MAX_SEARCH_LENGTH` in BruteForceParser addresses the compilation errors[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwithout touching external libraries or the fuzz harness.[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- By reusing `COSParser.DEFAULT_TRAIL_BYTECOUNT`, we preserve the existing [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mheuristic for how many trailing bytes should be buffered.[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Limiting the backward scan window maintains correctness—markers near the file end[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwill still be found—while preventing pathological full‐file scans that cause [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlibFuzzer timeouts.[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- All existing parser APIs and tests remain unchanged except for the introduction [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mof a getter and bounded‐search logic; no harness, utility, or test code is [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmodified.[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         ===[33mIssue[0m===                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ERROR: libFuzzer: timeout                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mReport[0m===                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         # Evaluation Report                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ## Summary                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         The project’s fuzzing harness reported a libFuzzer timeout when parsing certain PDF [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         inputs. To allow the `BruteForceParser` to bound its backward search from           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         end-of-file, a patch was proposed that [1m([0m[1;36m1[0m[1m)[0m adds a public `[1;35mgetFileLen[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m` accessor in [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `COSParser`, and [1m([0m[1;36m2[0m[1m)[0m introduces a new `MAX_SEARCH_LENGTH` constant in               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `BruteForceParser` initialized from `COSParser.DEFAULT_TRAIL_BYTECOUNT`. After      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         applying the patch, the build fails due to an access-control error:                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `DEFAULT_TRAIL_BYTECOUNT` is declared private in `COSParser` and cannot be          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         referenced from `BruteForceParser`.                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ## Description                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m. Initial Issue                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - ERROR: libFuzzer: timeout                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - This indicates that a fuzzing session against the PDF parser hung or ran out   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         of allotted time when exercising certain inputs.                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - No direct stack trace or exception was reported—only the fuzzer’s timeout      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         signal.                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m. Patch Attempt                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - In `COSParser.java` around line [1;36m207[0m:                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              • Closed an unbalanced brace.                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              • Added a public method:                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                ```                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                [35m/[0m**                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                 * Expose the underlying PDF length for bounded searches.                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                 *[35m/[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                public long [1;35mgetFileLen[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m [1m{[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                    return fileLen;                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                [1m}[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                ```                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - In `BruteForceParser.java` at the top:                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              • Introduced a private constant                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                `private static final long MAX_SEARCH_LENGTH =                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         COSParser.DEFAULT_TRAIL_BYTECOUNT;`                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                intended as the maximum number of bytes to scan backwards.                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - In the method that locates the EOF marker [1m([0maround line [1;36m525[0m[1m)[0m:                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              • Retrieved file length via `[1;35mparser.getFileLen[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m`.                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              • Computed `eofSearchStart` as either a fixed minimum offset                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1m([0m`MINIMUM_SEARCH_OFFSET`[1m)[0m or `fileLen – MAX_SEARCH_LENGTH`.                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              • Called `[1;35msource.seek[0m[1m([0meofSearchStart[1m)[0m` instead of always seeking to            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `MINIMUM_SEARCH_OFFSET`.                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m. Compilation Result                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Build failure in `BruteForceParser.java` pointing to the reference:            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              ```                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              COSParser.DEFAULT_TRAIL_BYTECOUNT                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              has private access in org.apache.pdfbox.pdfparser.COSParser                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              ```                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - The constant `DEFAULT_TRAIL_BYTECOUNT` cannot be accessed from another class   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         because it is declared private.                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - No other errors were reported, and the failure stops compilation at this       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         single access-control violation.                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m. Areas for Further Investigation                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Visibility of `DEFAULT_TRAIL_BYTECOUNT` in `COSParser`: Should it be made      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         public or should a new public constant be introduced?                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Initialization and usage of `fileLen` in `COSParser`: Confirm that `fileLen`   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         is correctly set before `[1;35mgetFileLen[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m` is called.                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Interaction between `BruteForceParser` and `COSParser`: Ensure that the parser [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         instance passed into `BruteForceParser` always has a valid file length.             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Potential side effects of changing seek offsets in `BruteForceParser`,         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         especially around edge cases near the file start or with very small files.          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ## Initial Issue Log                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         Here is the initial issue log of the codebase:                                      [2m                [0m
